properties.text: 1959 The Mini takes its debut drive on\nBritish roads, including the UK's first\nmotorway - the M1 - opening in November.

1954 Elvis Presley
releases his first
single 'That's All Right’,though 'the King's'
track does not reach the charts.

The Queen was crowned in June 1953
with 20 million people in the UK watching
it on televisions and a further 12.5 million
listening on radio. Cameras had never been
allowed in Westminster Abbey and the event
saw a boom in sales of the new technology.
